meanings.definition: To rate or evaluate as being higher or better than something else.
meanings.sent1: She outrated all her classmates in the math competition.
meanings.sent2: The new movie outrated the previous one in terms of box office earnings.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outrated the other animals in the race by finding a shortcut.
meanings.sent4: His dedication to his craft outrated anyone else's efforts.
meanings.sent5: The chef's dish outrated all others in flavor and presentation.

meanings.definition: To surpass in rating or evaluation.
meanings.sent1: The team outrated their opponents in every game this season.
meanings.sent2: Her performance outrated all expectations of the judges.
meanings.sent3: The cat outrated the dog in the cuteness contest.
meanings.sent4: His determination to succeed outrated any obstacles in his way.
meanings.sent5: The sunset outrated any painting with its vibrant colors.
